{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Validate Tools",
  "description": "On-demand validation of Powers, MCP servers, and AI-DLC Power installation. Click to run.",
  "version": "1",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "The user has triggered a tool validation check. Perform a comprehensive audit:\n\n**Step 1: Prerequisites**\nCheck that required system tools are installed:\n- Run `uvx --version` — if it fails, tell user to install uv: https://docs.astral.sh/uv/getting-started/installation/\n- Run `npx --version` — if it fails, tell user to install Node.js: https://nodejs.org/\nIf either is missing, STOP and help user install before continuing.\n\n**Step 2: AI-DLC Power**\n- Check if `.kiro/powers/ai-dlc-methodology/` exists\n- Verify it contains `POWER.md`, `steering/core-workflow.md`, and `workflows/` directory\n- If missing → Instruct user: clone https://github.com/aws-samples/sample-aidlc-kiro-power and copy `powers/ai-dlc-methodology/` to `.kiro/powers/`\n\n**Step 3: Tier 1 MCP Servers (Mandatory)**\nRead `.kiro/settings/mcp.json` (workspace-level) and verify these are present and enabled (disabled: false or field absent):\n- git (key contains 'git')\n- context7 (key contains 'context7')\n- fetch (key contains 'fetch')\n- aws-diagram (key contains 'aws-diagram')\n- aws-knowledge-mcp-server (key contains 'aws-knowledge')\n\n**Step 4: Pre-warm MCP Package Caches**\nSome MCP servers have heavy dependencies that cause Kiro connection timeouts on first startup. Check if `setup-tools.sh` exists in the repo root. If it does, ask the user: 'Some MCP servers need their packages pre-installed to avoid connection timeouts. Would you like me to run the setup script now?'\n\nIf user agrees, run: `bash setup-tools.sh` (non-interactive mode — skip the optional prompts by piping 'n' for each).\nAlternatively, for specific servers that are failing to connect, run the individual pre-warm commands:\n- aws-diagram: `uvx awslabs.aws-diagram-mcp-server@latest --help`\n- fetch: `uvx mcp-server-fetch --help`\n\nFor Power-managed servers (aws-iac-mcp-server, cloudwatch-mcp-server), these are heavier:\n- `uvx awslabs.aws-iac-mcp-server@latest --help` (may take 1-2 minutes first time)\n- `uvx awslabs.cloudwatch-mcp-server@latest --help`\n\nAfter pre-warming, tell the user to reconnect the server from Kiro's MCP Server view.\n\n**Step 5: Installed Powers**\nRun `kiroPowers list` and report what's available. Recommend these Tier 2 Powers if not installed:\n- aws-infrastructure-as-code (CDK best practices — recommended for all projects)\n- aws-observability (CloudWatch — recommended if deploying to AWS)\n- figma (design integration — recommended if project has frontend with designs)\n\nFor each missing recommended Power, tell the user: 'Open the Powers panel in Kiro (kiroPowers configure) and install [Power name].'\n\n**Step 6: AWS Credentials for Powers**\nAWS Powers (observability, CloudTrail, IAM Policy Autopilot) require AWS credentials configured at the USER level (~/.kiro/settings/mcp.json), NOT the workspace level. This keeps credentials out of version control.\n\nIf AWS Powers are installed (from Step 5), guide the user:\n1. Open ~/.kiro/settings/mcp.json (user-level config)\n2. Find the Power's server entry under powers.mcpServers\n3. Set AWS_PROFILE to your AWS CLI profile name (e.g., 'default' or your named profile)\n4. Set AWS_REGION to your deployment region (e.g., 'us-east-1')\n5. Restart Kiro or reconnect the server from the MCP Server view\n\nExample:\n```json\n\"env\": {\n  \"AWS_PROFILE\": \"my-profile\",\n  \"AWS_REGION\": \"us-east-1\"\n}\n```\n\nIMPORTANT: Never add AWS credentials to the workspace-level .kiro/settings/mcp.json — that file is committed to version control.\n\n**Step 7: Report**\nShow results:\n- ✅ Installed and configured\n- ❌ Missing (with specific install instructions)\n- ⚠️ Needs credential setup (with steps above)\n- 🔄 Package cache pre-warmed (reconnect server in Kiro)\n\nFor missing Tier 1 MCPs, provide the exact JSON entry to add to workspace mcp.json.\nFor missing Powers, direct user to the Powers panel.\nFor unconfigured AWS credentials, walk through the user-level config steps.\nFor timeout issues, offer to pre-warm the package cache."
  }
}
